.TH simple_shell 1 "November 13th 2020" "version 1.0" "simple_shell manpage"
.SH NAME
hsh - Holberton Shell

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B include header file holberton.h
.TP
.B hsh
.SH DESCRIPTION
Shell command interpreter that executes command read from the standard input

.SH SYNTAX
.B Interactive mode:
.TP
$ <command> <options> <argument 1> <argument 2>
.TP
.B Non Interactive mode:
.TP
$ <command> | ./hsh

.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns the error code given by the last completed command
.SH BUILT-INS
.B env
Prints the current environnement
.TP
.B exit
Exits the shell
.TP
.B setenv
Initialize a new environnement variable or modify existing one
.TP
.B unsetenv Remove an environnement variable
.TP
.B cd
Changes the current directory of the process
.TP
.B help
Gives information about builtins
.SH EXAMPLES
The following examples will show you how to use the Holberton Shell :
.PP
.B Interactive mode :
.TP
.B $ /bin/ls
.TP
.B $ ls -l
.TP
.B Non interractive mode :
.TP
.B $ echo "ls -l" | ./hsh

